main event: A sighting of a pseudo-satellite object observed in Oyster Bay, New York on August 17, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes., The object was reported to be descending., The observation was made visually., The object was described as a greenish-white light by one witness., The report was forwarded to the Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory for clarification.
witness description: A civilian observer who reported seeing a greenish-white light.
